<br>
Lets look at a lvl 40 Blademaster.<br>
33 Parry<br>
32 Celtic Dual<br>
32 Pierce<br>
Now here are my questions.<br>
<br>
1.  If this BM has +8 (40total) CD I know he does not get any styles higher then 32 but does he have the same chance to swing his off hand weapon as a lvl 40 BM with 40 trained Parry?<br>
<br>
2.  If this BM has +8 (40total) Pierce he doesn't get styles above 32 but does he deal teh same minimum damage as a lvl 40 BM who trained Pierce to 40?<br>
<br>
3.  And lastly if this BM has +7 (40total) to Parry does he have the same chance to parry attacks as a lvl 40 BM who trained to 40 in Parry?<br>
<br>
4.  Also am I to understand that being lvl 40 and having 45 total in Parry, for instance, with item bonuses does not actually help me past the 40th parry skill?  Such as if your skills are higher then your lvl the extra does not have any effect.<br>
<br>
I believe the answers to all of these are yes but want confermation from the seasoned Blademasters among me.  If you have any tips to throw my way (lvl 25 BM at the moment) do not hesitate to type them out.<br>
Thank you in advance for the help.<br>
