<br>
I've never heard a firm answer whether parry, block, or CD/DW over 50 does anything.  I suspect each point of parry and block is work 0.5% up to 50 and 0.1% over 50, but I've never seen Mythic give a straight answer.<br>
<br>
Also, be aware that speccing CD does very little for damage.  Because your offhand lacks the to-hit and damage bonuses from styles, an off-hand swing isn't worth nearly as much as a main-hand swing.  The best numbers have a point of CD spec adding a 0.65% chance to swing your offhand, which is a 0.3%-0.4% increase in total damage.  A point of pierce (under 50) will increase your damage by 3-4% easy, 10 times as useful as CD.<br>
<br>
Weapon skill over 50 has been well-studied, and each point adds 1%-1.5% to your total damage.  Not great, but still a bunch more useful than CD.<br>
<br>
